    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-25T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-25T02:00:00-05:00" n="211"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW 1939/8–2544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé Near the Yugoslav Government in Exile</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-25T10:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 25, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 25—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yugos 136. Message from King Michael for Stirbey received by Cretzianu 8:30 p.m.
                    Wednesday, 23rd, shortly before proclamation <pb facs="0205" n="195"
                        xml:id="pg_195"/> of break will [<hi rend="italic">with</hi>] Axis, states
                    that in view of decisive action which will take place in Rumania on Saturday
                    August 26 he requests, in conformity with promise of General Wilson, a massive
                    bombardment of numerous specified places in Rumania and Hungary.</p>
                <p>This message, which was received here and sent to AFHQ Caserta yesterday, makes
                    it appear that Rumanian break was planned for tomorrow and that events forced
                    prior action.</p>
                <p>De Chastelain<note n="87" xml:id="d211fn1">British lieutenant colonel in
                        Rumania.</note> and two Rumanian staff officers reached Ankara
                    yesterday.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Murphy as number 15 and to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shantz</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
